$ Powershell: items

An item is one of
  • → Windows/PowerShell/language/alias[alias]
  • → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable[variable]
  • → Windows/PowerShell/language/statement/function[function]
  • Environment variable
  • file
  • directory

All items are identified by a *data store* and a *path name*.

The path name consists of *→ Windows/PowerShell/language/provider/drive[drive] name*, *item name* and *(sub-)containers*.
-
A path name is either *fully qualified* or *relative*.
-
Thus, path name very much resemble ordinary file system paths.


